---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
	title="Governance | The Sovereign Protocol of Tadpole OS"
	description="The ethical and technical framework for local-first multi-agent systems. Understanding the Overlord Protocol and Sovereign Execution."
>
	<main class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="space-y-12">
      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="space-y-4 border-b border-white/5 pb-12">
        <a href="./" class="text-[10px] font-mono text-zinc-500 hover:text-emerald-400 transition-colors flex items-center gap-2 tracking-widest uppercase">
          ← Return to Base
        </a>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-7xl font-bold tracking-tighter text-white">
          The <span class="text-zinc-600">Sovereign Protocol</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xs text-emerald-500/60 font-mono tracking-[0.2em] uppercase">
          Version 1.0.0 | Governance & Ethics Whitepaper
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Section: The Overlord -->
      <section class="space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold border-l border-emerald-500/30 pl-6 text-white tracking-tight">I. The Overlord (Entity 0)</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed space-y-4 font-light">
          <p>
            In the Tadpole OS ecosystem, the human operator is designated as **Entity 0**, also known as **The Overlord**. This role is the final authority in our parallel intelligence layer.
          </p>
          <div class="glass-surface p-8 rounded-2xl space-y-4 mt-8">
            <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-emerald-400 uppercase tracking-widest">Authority Protocols</h4>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-3 text-sm">
              <li><strong>Final Authority</strong>: No agent may execute a destructive or high-risk tool without explicit encryption-checked approval from Entity 0.</li>
              <li><strong>Strategic Directive</strong>: Intelligence flows downward. The Overlord provides the "Global Intent," which is recursively decomposed by sub-agents into tactical execution steps.</li>
              <li><strong>The Safety Gate</strong>: A dedicated Oversight Dashboard ensures every LLM-generated decision is visible, auditable, and retractable in real-time.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Section: Local-First Sovereignty -->
      <section class="space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold border-l border-emerald-500/30 pl-6 text-white tracking-tight">II. Sovereign Execution</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed space-y-4 font-light">
          <p>
            Tadpole OS operates on the principle of **Absolute Data Sovereignty**. We believe companies shouldn't have to "rent" their strategic intelligence from Big Tech intermediaries.
          </p>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 my-8">
            <div class="p-8 glass-surface rounded-2xl relative overflow-hidden group">
              <div class="absolute -right-4 -top-4 w-16 h-16 bg-emerald-500/5 blur-2xl group-hover:bg-emerald-500/10 transition-colors"></div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-white mb-2 tracking-tight">Private Context</h4>
              <p class="text-xs text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed italic">"Your intelligence, your hardware." - Every strategic directive and proprietary context remains local, protected by NeuralVault encryption.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-8 glass-surface rounded-2xl relative overflow-hidden group">
              <div class="absolute -right-4 -top-4 w-16 h-16 bg-emerald-500/5 blur-2xl group-hover:bg-emerald-500/10 transition-colors"></div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-white mb-2 tracking-tight">Moral Moat</h4>
              <p class="text-xs text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed italic">By automating the drudgery, we secure the future for your employees. Growth is used to build a legacy, not cut costs.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Section: Scaling Small Teams -->
      <section class="space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold border-l border-emerald-500/30 pl-6 text-white tracking-tight">III. The Scalability Matrix</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed space-y-4 font-light">
          <p>
            From a single **Tadpole** pilot in a Windows Sandbox to a massive **Big Frog** swarm in a production Bunker.
          </p>
          <blockquote class="border-l-2 border-emerald-500/20 pl-8 italic text-lg text-zinc-200 my-12 font-light leading-relaxed">
            "The future of business belongs to small, agile teams wielding massive, sovereign intelligence swarms."
          </blockquote>
          <p>
            By leveraging Rust-powered concurrency, SMEs can recruit 25+ specialist agents simultaneously, solving a month's work in an hour with zero latency bottlenecks.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Footer CTA -->
      <footer class="pt-24 border-t border-white/5 text-center space-y-12 pb-12">
        <p class="text-zinc-600 font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.4em] uppercase">© 2026 Tadpole OS | Sovereign Protocol V1.0</p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
          <a href="https://github.com/DDS-Solutions/TadPole-OS" class="w-full sm:w-auto px-10 py-4 bg-white text-zinc-950 font-bold rounded-xl hover:bg-zinc-200 transition-all hover:scale-105 active:scale-95 shadow-[0_0_20px_rgba(255,255,255,0.1)] text-sm">
            Start the Pilot
          </a>
          <a href="./" class="w-full sm:w-auto px-10 py-4 glass-surface text-zinc-400 font-bold rounded-xl hover:bg-white/5 transition-all text-sm">
            Back to Home
          </a>
        </div>
      </footer>
    </div>
	</main>
</BaseLayout>
